cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about abstractive text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses reinforcement learning and adversarial training, which are common techniques in machine learning, so it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves text generation and information retrieval, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of a discriminator in the adversarial process suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
